We exclude patients for whom it is impossible to determine the date of the FollowUp

Lets find the maximum date, which we will take as the database closure date

## [1] "2022-03-03 UTC"

Lets calculate the time until death and impute the data to those whose death we know about, but do not know the date

## [1] 106.5

Where there is no last visit and the date of death is unknown, we impute the median time to death, provided that the patient is known to have died.

Where there is a last visit, but the date of death is unknown, we substitute the midpoint of the time between the patients last visit and the closing of the database (the most recent visit of all)

Now lets check whether all situations can be processed in this way
